%% Training Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / kubectl
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as Training Operator<br/>Controller
    participant Pods as Worker/Master Pods
    participant HeadlessSvc as Headless Service<br/>(DNS discovery)

    Note over User,HeadlessSvc: Flow 1: Training Job Submission
    User->>K8sAPI: POST PyTorchJob CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kubeconfig
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-pytorchjob<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed CA)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response (allow/deny)
    K8sAPI-->>User: Created / Rejected

    Note over User,HeadlessSvc: Flow 2: PyTorchJob Reconciliation
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch notification (Informer)<br/>TLS 1.2+ / ServiceAccount token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create/Update HPA (elastic)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Pods (Master + Workers)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Headless Service<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update Job Status<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+

    Note over User,HeadlessSvc: Flow 3: Distributed Training (inter-worker)
    Pods->>HeadlessSvc: DNS lookup for peer workers
    HeadlessSvc-->>Pods: Pod IP addresses
    Pods->>Pods: TCP 23456 (PyTorch default)<br/>Plaintext / NetworkPolicy enforced
